        "content": "<p>Are 'formal limit' and 'formal colimit' sufficiently precise and recognised terms to require an nLab page? They crop up here and there,  such as on <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/ind-pro-object\">[[ind-pro-object]]</a>.</p>",
        "id": 496275572,
        "sender_full_name": "David Corfield",
        "timestamp": 1738051061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For context, I was looking to understand this <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/a/28858/447\">MO answer</a>:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/JtuEiY0T7XCHZKsakVGDrvqU/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/JtuEiY0T7XCHZKsakVGDrvqU/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"684x172\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/21317/JtuEiY0T7XCHZKsakVGDrvqU/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 496276018,
        "sender_full_name": "David Corfield",
        "timestamp": 1738051229
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess the definition would be that a \"formal colimit of Xs\" is an object of the free cocompletion of the category of Xs under some class of colimits?</p>",
        "id": 496276364,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1738051404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just as you might define a \"formal sum\" of elements of some set <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> to be an element of the free abelian group generated by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 496276483,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1738051447
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Seems like a reasonable topic for a page to me.  I wonder if there's something more general to be said about the meaning of the word \"formal\".</p>",
        "id": 496276573,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1738051501
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, so we're seeing instances such as <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/pro-object\">[[pro-object]]</a> where the class of limit is mentioned:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A <strong>pro-object</strong> of a category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> is a \"formal filtered limit\" of objects of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 496277368,
        "sender_full_name": "David Corfield",
        "timestamp": 1738051856
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would be tempted just to redirect those terms to <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/free%20cocompletion\">[[free cocompletion]]</a>.</p>",
        "id": 496289595,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
